# Git

- Commit and push **only** when the user explicitly asks.
- Never update `git config`, skip hooks, force-push `main`, or run destructive git commands unless explicitly requested.
- Messages: lowercase, imperative (`add …`, `fix …`, `remove …`). No `feat:`/`fix:` prefixes. One line; focus on why, not file lists.
- Before committing: `git status`, `git diff`, `git log`. Stage only relevant files. No secrets.
